# Evergreen Robot Platform Architecture
## Sell Once, Revenue Forever — The Skeleton Economy

**Date conceived:** 2026-07-10  
**Author:** Bryan Robert Horsfield 
**Status:** Prior art declaration

---

## Core Concept

A humanoid robot platform designed for permanent relevance through
radical upgradeability. The skeleton is engineered once, engineered
right, and sold at cost or below. All revenue comes from the
ecosystem built on top of it.

Not a product. A platform.
Not a sale. A relationship.
Not a robot. A childhood friend.

---

## The Architecture

### The Skeleton
The permanent, load-bearing investment:
- Engineered to last decades
- Standardised joints, connectors, power systems
- Hydraulic actuator-based (variable compliance, pressure feedback,
  sealed circuits — see hydraulic-expansion-chamber-actuator.md)
- Designed for disassembly and reassembly in minutes
- All parts interchangeable across all units in the fleet
- One platform. Every expression built on top of it.

### The Ecosystem Layer
Everything above the skeleton is modular, replaceable, and
monetisable:
- **Skins** — aesthetic outer shells, themed, branded, seasonal
- **Personalities** — software-defined character, tone, behaviour
- **Tool attachments** — task-specific end effectors and accessories
- **Capability upgrades** — new motor assemblies, sensor packages
- **Third party integrations** — open platform for accessory ecosystem
- **Firmware and AI updates** — continuous intelligence improvement

The skeleton is the razor. The ecosystem is the blades.

