## Revenue Model

### One-Time
- Skeleton sale (at cost or subsidised) — acquisition vehicle

### Recurring Monthly
- Care refresh subscription — $50/month per unit
- Personality subscription — software-defined character updates
- Third party ecosystem clip — percentage of accessory sales

### Annual
- Service interval — skeleton swap, battery, uprated parts, firmware
- Skin refresh — new aesthetic season/theme

### Ecosystem
- Third party tool and accessory marketplace
- Developer platform fees
- Enterprise customisation licensing

### Data
- Anonymised interaction and training data (with consent)
  — most valuable asset in the long term

---

## Scale Economics

At 100,000,000 units:
- Care refresh alone: $5B/month
- Annual service: significant per-unit revenue × 100M events/year
- Accessory ecosystem: unbounded third party expansion
- Training data value: potentially exceeds hardware revenue

The skeleton is almost irrelevant financially.
The platform is everything.

